,Recommended,247910,32213541,Posted: 5 June,all,LockeProposal,"Atmospheric & pregnant with tension // Recommended if playing co-op with friends*You'd likely prefer to pick this one up at sale price+ You can press CTRL to aim rifles without the scope; very useful in situations where one is cornered with only a primary+ Desolate environments with much attention paid to detail+ Genuinely creepy atmosphere; can prove to be very stressful in a way that is immersive+ Gunplay & general mechanics are crisp and responsive+ Bullet cam is a delight during combat, though it does get a bit old later on; fortunately, the frequency of its use can be adjusted in the settings+ Background dialogue in the safehouses is extremely well-done; very immersive- Looks and feels almost identical to the original- Multiplayer is basically deserted; co-op adds so much to the value, but you'll be relying on direct friend invites- Cover mechanics are clunky & largely unnecessary; there are so few enemies that have ranged attacks that this may as well have not been included in the final product- Shallow, lifeless plot & characters- Short length (about 6 hours to complete the campaign playing solo)LockeProposal's Big Day OutCommunity GroupCurator PageSerious Steam Reviews subReddit"
