76561198089052394,Recommended,247910,31232548,Posted: 19 April,all,JD Herrera,"Sniper Elite: Nazi Zombie Army 2		* 7/10The Nazi Zombie Army is back and angrier than before, but we're ready to take them downThere's no need to go in depth, nor to say too much. The plot of the game goes ahead, but just like in the first chapter that's more like a pretext to make you face Nazi zombies together with your friends. This is the kind of game you just play and have fun because you play with friends and it doesn't need any particular story, nor complicated mechanics, just go and shoot or snipe on the hordes, that's all, really. Why the fun? Friends of mine just love wave based coop games... Or zombie games. I can live with it but I've been simply struck by the 80's synth music and that foggy atmosphere that really reminds me of Carpenter's movies. That's my weak point: 80s. Believe me or not that made the difference to me with other common games: the opportunity to play with friends against nazi zombies in foggy villages with an 80's synth music.I could spend a couple of words about the awesomeness of the slowmotion effect during successful sniping shots and the x-ray cam to see which bone has been broken by our bullet, but that's not the news, something already seen and already done, in Sniper Elite v2 or in Mortal Kombat as well.The most important thing I can say is that this is the second chapter, which comes after the first chapter (of course) and there's also a trilogy chapter, which holds the first, second and third exclusive episode in an improved engine (not much, just a little bit).So while I recommend this game, I actually recommend you to buy directly the trilogy because this situation doesn't make much sense at all...+++PROs+++ZOMBIES... NAZIS! COOP!!!Facing Hordes of Nazi Zombies with your friends? You've just nailed it, without anything too complicated.ATMOSPHERE.Foggy roads and villages, rubbles in towns everything while you listen to some 80's synth music. Simply perfect!---CONs---MANEUVERABILITY.A common problem with Sniper elite 1 and V2, the caracter's moves can be a bit too rigid sometimes, and it may cost you your life while you're surrounded by zombies.MEANINGLESS EPISODIC PRODUCT.For some odd *cough*MONEY*cough* reason they released the first and the second chapter on their own. Then they released a trilogy with both of them and the final chapter. No discounts for those who already owned the first 2 chapters, no single third chapter as well... None of the two chapter is worth buying, it makes more sense to take the entire trilogy.I played this game on this machine:Intel Core i7-497016Gb RAM DDR3GeForce GTX 660Windows 10 Professional x64"
