76561197999135246,Recommended,247910,9301897,"Posted: 1 March, 2014",all,BrokenRetina,"I've played pt 1. I really enjoyed it even though it felt quite incomplete at the end. I've played pt 2 for maybe 10 mins and I can already say I'm pretty disappointed. Not in the game in general, but in the fact that they've released a game that doesn't really include anything new in terms of weapons/story and not really any new mechanics (which is not really as important in a sniper elite mod/ expansion). Sure, they released a new campaign which I've yet to fully experience, but this game, if anything, should've been an add-on to the original Nazi Zombie Army. The series itself appeals to me because the zombies are the slow shambling type and headshots are completely required to survive which makes it a bit ""realistic"" and the sniping x-ray mechanic is really awesome. I can't recommend this game to someone that's already bought pt 1 unless they really enjoyed it like I did. As for people that haven't played pt 1 I'd recommend this game but only after u've watched a few youtube vids and if u've got a few extra dollars lying around. As for everyone, just to prove a point to the develepor, only buy this game on a steam sale like i did. I'm sure u will enjoy it solo like I did and love it playing co-op, but still, just buy this game on sale.Graphics are good so long as you have a decent graphics card cuz it runs really well on my pc which has a nvidia gtx 560ti. Anything below that, just be careful. a lot of people that have posted reviews here stating that it's not properly optimized. It runs very well for me on high settings.I would give this a thumbs down because it's a ♥♥♥♥ING expansion to NZ1 but I've enjoyed the series enough to give it a thumbs up. Just don't pay $15 for it. Support the developer, not for a $15 expansion, but for the idea that a pretty cool zombie $15 game could be expanded upon. Buy it. Only on a decent steam sale."
