,Recommended,247910,9366466,"Posted: 6 March, 2014",all,dethb0y,"Me and a friend snagged this when it was on sale, and played through it over the course of 3-4 days. The individual missions are few, but very long. There's a few annoyances (If you die, you can't rejoin a game in progress, and you can't save in the middle of the missions between sessions). But overall, the experience was tremendously enjoyable and entertaining.The game play is mostly of the form ""go from A to B, through a horde of zombies"". Sometimes you have to do ""seiges"" in which a bunch of zombies spawn and you have to kill them. At all points it felt pretty organic - you just go around killing zombies as you see best, and you're not really locked into any given strategy most of the time. There's a variety of weapons (Sniper Rifles, SMG's, and pistols are your guns, while you have trip mines, land mines, grenades (2 types) and dynamite for your explosives and traps. You can also get two types of shotguns (though only off the ground in some missions). The gun handling is superb, as you'd expect.I recommend it, especially if you like zombie games, or sniping games (though there are few chances for real long-range sniping)."
